<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
1. 13. 1. 
<taxonomicName LSID="794135D6-7249-5755-847C-267558EB5D76" authority="(Rich.) Amshoff var. virgata" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dioclea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dioclea virgata subsp. var. var. virgata" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="virgata" subSpecies="var." variety="virgata">Dioclea virgata (Rich.) Amshoff var. virgata</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dioclea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dioclea lasiocarpa" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiocarpa">Dioclea lasiocarpa</taxonomicName>
Mart. ex Benth., Comm. Legum. Gen.: 69. 1837. Type: Brazil, Bahia, Salvador (
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Soteropolis’">'Soteropolis'</normalizedToken>
), 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Martius s.n. Obs. 2016</emphasis>
(lectotype, designated here amongst the syntypes: M! [0240665]; isolectotypes: M! [0240664], M! [0240663]). Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Bentham, G" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refId="B7" refString="Bentham, G, 1837. Commentationes de Leguminosarum Generibus. Zollinger, Vienna, 1-488." title="Commentationes de Leguminosarum Generibus. Zollinger, Vienna, 1 - 488." year="1837">Bentham (1837)</bibRefCitation>
did not cite any specimen for his species 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="D." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. lasiocarpa" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="lasiocarpa">D. lasiocarpa</taxonomicName>
. He recognised three unnamed varieties (α, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="β">β</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="ɣ">ɣ</normalizedToken>
); we selected the specimen cited for var. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘α’">'α'</normalizedToken>
as the lectotype of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName authority="Walpers, 1840" authorityName="Walpers" authorityYear="1840" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crepidotropis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Crepidotropis brasiliensis" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Crepidotropis brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
Walpers, Linnaea 14: 296. 1840. Type: Brazil, Bahia, Cruz de Casma [probably Salvador], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Luschnath s.n.</emphasis>
(lectotype, designated here amongst the isotypes: HAL! [0120300]; isolectotype: LE). Note: 
<bibRefCitation author="Maxwell, RH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refId="B35" refString="Maxwell, RH, 1969. The genus Dioclea (Fabaceae) in the New World. PhD Dissertation, Southern Illinois University, Carbondale, U.S.A." title="The genus Dioclea (Fabaceae) in the New World. PhD Dissertation, Southern Illinois University, Carbondale, U. S. A." year="1969">Maxwell (1969)</bibRefCitation>
said that duplicates in LE are annotated with different numbers (#206, #781, #2054), but probably from the same gathering.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Canavalia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Canavalia bracteolata" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bracteolata">Canavalia bracteolata</taxonomicName>
Merrill, J. Straits Br. Royal As. Soc. 86: 313. 1922. Type: Malaysia, Sabah, Sandakan, (Borneo), 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Ramos 1511</emphasis>
(holotype: PHN; isotypes: A! [00059980], BM! [000958604], GH! [00059979], K! [000898374], L! [0018940], P! [00708471], US! [00004634]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Canavalia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Canavalia peruviana" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peruviana">Canavalia peruviana</taxonomicName>
Piper, Publ. Field Mus. Bot. 4: 94. 1925. Type: Peru, La Merced, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Macbride 5551</emphasis>
(holotype: F! [0043480F]; isotypes: G! [00364938], US! [00004655]).
</paragraph>
